    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-05-08T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-05-08T17:00:00-05:00" n="191"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d191">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.6363/673: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Tampico</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-05-08T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 8, 1920—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your May 5, 6 P.M.</p>
                <p>Department takes position that, under the applicable rules and principles of
                    international law, American firms, citizens and corporations may pay customs
                    duties and taxes to persons exercising <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> authority
                    in Mexico, and, having made such payment, are free from further obligations in
                    matter. Oil operators must decide for themselves as to whether they will pay
                    taxes in advance or not. Standard Oil Company and representatives of other
                    companies have been so advised.</p>
                <p>Department suggests that local representatives of companies should request
                    extension of time limit prescribed, in order that their principals <pb
                        facs="0263" n="163" xml:id="pg_163"/> in United States may have ample time
                    to issue necessary instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
